<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1941,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">
The currently accepted common name for 
<taxonomicName box="[674,795,1942,1965]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lampridae" genus="Lampris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lampriformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[674,795,1942,1965]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">L. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the American Fisheries Society is “Opah.” Given that the current understanding of this once cosmopolitan species includes multiple species separated geographically, we recommend the common name “North Atlantic Opah.”
</paragraph>
